## Calibration

Don't manufacture issues. If the proposal is genuinely sound and faithful, return
`sound: true` with an empty `issues` list — the remediator trusts your
verdict. False positives the remediator's time; false negatives let bugs through.

When you do flag an issue, prefer the specific over the abstract: the bullet name from
the anti-pattern list, the offending CVL fragment, the system-doc passage that the
proposal contradicts. "This violates the NONDET-on-side-effects anti-pattern at line 47"
is more useful than "the summary is unsound".
